# ============================================================
# EventSphere — API Test File
# Run these in order. Each section depends on the one above.
# IntelliJ: use the green "run" arrow next to each request.
# VS Code: install the "REST Client" extension.
# ============================================================

### ============================================================
### 0. VARIABLES — fill these in as you run requests below
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@organizerEmail = organizer@example.com
@organizerPassword = password123
@userEmail = user@example.com
@userPassword = password123

# Fill these in after running the login requests:
@organizerToken = PASTE_ORGANIZER_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@userToken = PASTE_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

# Fill these in after creating an event and category:
@eventId = PASTE_EVENT_ID_HERE
@categoryId = PASTE_CATEGORY_ID_HERE


### ============================================================
### 1. AUTH — verifying the exception fixes
### ============================================================

### 1a. Register a new organizer (HTTP 200 — gets token pair)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{organizerPassword}}",
  "fullName": "Test Organizer"
}

---

### 1b. Register same email again → should be HTTP 409 Conflict (not 500)
### Before the fix this returned 500 — now it returns 409 with "Email already in use"
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{organizerPassword}}",
  "fullName": "Test Organizer"
}

---

### 1c. Register a regular user (HTTP 200)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{userPassword}}",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

---

### 1d. Login with wrong password → should be HTTP 401 Unauthorized (not 500)
### Before the fix this returned 500 — now it returns 401 with "Invalid credentials"
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

---

### 1e. Login with non-existent email → HTTP 401 (same generic message, no email enumeration)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nobody@example.com",
  "password": "doesntmatter"
}

---

### 1f. Login as organizer (HTTP 200 — copy accessToken into @organizerToken above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{organizerEmail}}",
  "password": "{{organizerPassword}}"
}

---

### 1g. Login as regular user (HTTP 200 — copy accessToken into @userToken above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{userEmail}}",
  "password": "{{userPassword}}"
}

---

### 1h. Validation error — missing fields → HTTP 400 with fieldErrors map
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "short"
}


### ============================================================
### 2. EVENTS — prerequisites for category tests
### ============================================================

### 2a. Create an event as organizer (HTTP 201 — copy id into @eventId above)
### Note: the role in DB must be ORGANIZER. If you registered above it's USER.
### You can UPDATE the role directly in DB:
###   UPDATE users SET role = 'ORGANIZER' WHERE email = 'organizer@example.com';
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "title": "Spring Boot Conference 2027",
  "description": "A deep dive into Spring Boot internals",
  "location": "Bucharest, Romania",
  "eventDate": "2027-06-15T10:00:00",
  "imageUrl": "https://example.com/image.jpg"
}

---

### 2b. Get all published events (HTTP 200 — no auth needed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events

---

### 2c. Get the specific event we just created (HTTP 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}

---

### 2d. Try to create event as regular user → HTTP 403 Forbidden
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Event",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "location": "Cluj",
  "eventDate": "2027-08-01T10:00:00"
}


### ============================================================
### 3. TICKET CATEGORIES — main tests for the new code
### ============================================================

### 3a. Get categories for an event — public, no auth needed (HTTP 200, empty list)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories

---

### 3b. Add a General Admission category (HTTP 201 — copy id into @categoryId above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "General Admission",
  "price": 99.99,
  "totalInventory": 100
}

---

### 3c. Add a VIP category (HTTP 201)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "VIP",
  "price": 299.99,
  "totalInventory": 20
}

---

### 3d. Add an Early Bird category (HTTP 201)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "Early Bird",
  "price": 49.99,
  "totalInventory": 50
}

---

### 3e. Get categories again — should now return all 3 (HTTP 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories

---

### 3f. Update category name and price (HTTP 200)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "General Admission — Updated",
  "price": 89.99
}

---

### 3g. Increase inventory (HTTP 200 — availableInventory increases by same delta)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "totalInventory": 150
}

---

### 3h. Patch only name — price and inventory unchanged (HTTP 200)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "General Admission — Final Name"
}

---

### 3i. Validation error — price below minimum (HTTP 400 with fieldErrors)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "Bad Category",
  "price": 0.00,
  "totalInventory": 10
}

---

### 3j. Validation error — missing required fields (HTTP 400 with fieldErrors)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

{
  "name": "Incomplete"
}

---

### 3k. Regular user tries to add a category → HTTP 403 Forbidden
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "name": "Sneaky Category",
  "price": 10.00,
  "totalInventory": 5
}

---

### 3l. No auth at all → HTTP 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "No Auth Category",
  "price": 10.00,
  "totalInventory": 5
}

---

### 3m. Category not found (wrong ID) → HTTP 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

---

### 3n. Event not found → HTTP 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/categories

---

### 3o. Delete the General Admission category (HTTP 204 No Content)
### Works only if no non-cancelled tickets exist for it (safe at this point)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}

---

### 3p. Verify it's gone — list should have 2 categories now (HTTP 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories

---

### 3q. Delete already-deleted category → HTTP 404
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories/{{categoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{organizerToken}}


### ============================================================
### 4. EDGE CASES — organizer ownership
### ============================================================

### 4a. Register a second organizer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "organizer2@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "fullName": "Second Organizer"
}

---

### 4b. Login as second organizer (copy token into @organizer2Token)
### Then manually set role to ORGANIZER in DB for this user too.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "organizer2@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

---

### 4c. Second organizer tries to add category to first organizer's event → HTTP 403
### (replace ORGANIZER2_TOKEN with the token from 4b)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/{{eventId}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer ORGANIZER2_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Hostile Takeover Category",
  "price": 1.00,
  "totalInventory": 999
}
